Description:
Ballistics of 115x728R 3UBK7 with the 3BK15 "Zmeya" HEAT-FS projectile, fired from the U-5TS tank gun (GRAU index 2A20). Introduced alongside "Ikra" (100mm D-10T), "Kadet" (100mm T-12), "Nadezha" (125mm), and adopted betweten 1975 and 1978. Projectile includes spiked nosecone.

Round   Proj.   Liner
3UBK7   3BK15   Steel
3UBK7M  3BK15M  Copper

Projectile inset approximately 1.3 dm into cartridge, 1.35 dm³ deducted from chamber volume. Per АРТИЛЛЕРИЙСКИЕ МЕТАТЕЛЬНЫЕ ЗАРЯДЫ, the following variation of performance with temperature is known:

T  V   P.mcp 
°C m/s kgf/cm² MPa
-40 1014 2200
15  1060 2650 290 
40  1089 3000

Pressure converted from copper crusher gauge to piezoelectric value (0.098 x 1.12) in MPa. Charge mass is fitted to yield the requisite muzzle velocity.
